physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Color fundus photography showed a cherry-red spot with a ring of whitish infiltrate surrounding both macula. Optical Coherence Tomography (OCT) revealed a thickening and increased reflectivity of the inner retinal layers with a shadowing effect on the outer structures. The marked thickening and hyperreflective part was within a 1-2 papillary diameter (PD) area around the fovea.
